---
# User Configuration for odoo-docker plugin
# Copy this file to ~/.claude/odoo-docker.local.md and customize.
# The skill reads these values to personalize generated configs.

# Docker Hub image prefix (your org or username)
image_prefix: "myorg/odoo"

# Default Odoo version when not auto-detected
default_version: "17"

# Default HTTP port for new projects
default_http_port: 8069

# PostgreSQL default credentials (override for security)
default_db_user: "odoo"
default_db_password: "odoo"

# Git org for source cloning suggestions
git_org: "my-github-org"

# Volume paths (relative to project root)
source_path: "./sources"
projects_path: "./projects"
conf_path: "./conf"
logs_path: "./logs"
---

# Odoo Docker — User Configuration

This file customizes the `odoo-docker` plugin for your environment.
Edit the YAML frontmatter above to match your setup.

## Image Prefix

The `image_prefix` controls Docker image tags in generated configs:
- `"myorg/odoo"` produces `myorg/odoo:19.0-enterprise`
- `"ghcr.io/myorg/odoo"` produces `ghcr.io/myorg/odoo:19.0-enterprise`

## Port Allocation

When running multiple projects, ports increment by 100:
- Project 1: HTTP 8069, Gevent 8072
- Project 2: HTTP 8169, Gevent 8172
- Project 3: HTTP 8269, Gevent 8272

Change `default_http_port` to shift the starting range.

## Credentials

For production, always override `default_db_password` with a strong password.
The plugin will remind you if defaults are detected in production configs.
